Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Drain and rinse @chickpeas{1%can}; pat dry with #paper towels{}. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%oz} on a diagonal into ½-inch pieces (halve lengthwise first if carrots are on the larger side).

Toss chickpeas on one side of a #baking sheet{} with half the @veggie stock concentrate{1}, half the @shawarma spice blend{1%tbsp}, a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss carrots on empty side of sheet with remaining @veggie stock concentrate{1}, @shawarma spice blend{1%tbsp}, another drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until chickpeas are browned and crispy and carrots are browned and tender, ~{18-22%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, half the @chili powder{1%tsp} (you'll use more later), remaining stock concentrate, @water{1 1/4%cups} (2 1/4 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to simmer; cover and cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, finely chop @parsley{1/4%oz}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Mince @jalapeño{1}, removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Roughly chop @pistachios{1/2%oz}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with paper towels and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

== Schug Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #medium pan{} over high heat. Add @grape tomatoes{4%oz}; cook, stirring occasionally, until blistered, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove pan from heat; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine parsley, half the @garlic powder{1%tsp}, remaining @chili powder{1%tsp}, @olive oil{1 1/2%tbsp} (3 TBSP for 4 servings), a big squeeze of lemon juice, and as much jalapeño as you like. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Lemon Aioli ==

In a separate small bowl, combine @vegan mayo{4%tbsp}, remaining garlic powder, @sugar{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4), a squeeze of lemon juice, and a pinch of lemon zest. Add @water{1%tsp} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in a drizzle of @olive oil{2 1/2%tsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with chickpeas, carrots, and tomatoes. Drizzle everything with lemon aioli and schug sauce. Garnish with pistachios and serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

Slice chicken crosswise; serve atop bowls.